Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper presents a new block encryption system and compares its performance against a well-known encryption algorithm using statistical tests. This is a clear indication that the paper belongs to the Cryptography and Security sub-category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of quasigroups in block encryption, which is related to information theory and coding theory. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve discussions on the computational complexity of the proposed algorithm and its efficiency compared to AES256.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may discuss the use of the proposed algorithm in sensor networks, which is related to systems and control.
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper may discuss the use of the proposed algorithm in sensor networks, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
